THIS GLOBE OF THE EARTH-
is steel; weight 3¼ tons;
diameter 10 feet; circumference 31 feet, 5 Inches.
Shows airlines of the world, in addition to chief
geographical features, including ocean depths.
The globe is oriented so that its axis parallels
the axis of the earth undertoot, its North Pole
pointing to the North Star.
On this scale (linch to 64 miles) the greatest
ocean depth, 34,218 feet just east of the Philip-
pines- would be only ½ of an inch below the
surface of this ball, showing that, compared with
the bulk of the earth, the great oceans are
relatively only a thin covering of water.
The deepest man has gone beneath the surface of
the earth (William Beebe, who descended 2,200 feet
into the ocean at Bermuda) would on this scale be
scarcely through the paint - so of an inch down.
